Hastings Bedroom is a room with the printed name "The Guest Bedroom (Poirot's Flat)". "[first time]I had awoken later than usual that morning and felt remarkably well-rested. I was raring to take a leisurely constitutional with Bob before breakfast and subsequently bring the family out to the park. These pleasurable thoughts were banished in short order as I looked out the window to witness London weather at its most miserable. Subdued but determined to make the best of it, I swiftly prepared to face the day.

