The description of Hercule Poirot is "[one of]Poirot and I were a study in contrasts. The man was no taller than five feet, five inches, and had always possessed a delicately plump frame (which had grown slightly plumper of late, to his dismay). His attire was unapologetically foreign and dandified, subject at all times to his mania for neatness. He was by turns coolly commanding and demonstrative to an embarrassing degree. In spite of our many differences, we had become the dearest of friends in the pursuit of our shared interest in detection.[or]To speak of Poirot without mentioning his luxuriant moustaches is to commit a grave omission. He was inordinately proud of them, keeping them trimmed and pomaded in a supremely symmetrical manner. His black hair, which nowadays had mostly receded to the sides of his head and was slicked back gracefully, had also once been parted right down the middle. It could be difficult to take my friend seriously when his primness and vanity were manifesting in full force[unicode 8212]however, I had come to realize that he actually preferred to be underestimated, and deemed it a valuable tactical advantage.[or]Whiskers aside, another noteworthy feature of Poirot's was his hazel eyes, which at times appear to shine bright green[unicode 8212]most frequently when seizing onto something significant, and sometimes accompanied by an enigmatic Cheshire-cat smile. It could be quite disarming to be the focus of his piercing gaze.[or]My friend’s hands have often captivated me. Their steadiness was such that he could easily build card houses a dozen stories high, and his sleight of hand never failed to amaze us all. He gestured with them eloquently whenever he was excited or agitated, and connected their legendary exactitude to a corresponding precision of the brain[unicode 8212]a common theme with Poirot.[or]I took a closer look at what my friend was currently wearing[unicode 8212]a dark waistcoat over a white high-collared shirt, a paisley bowtie, perfectly-pressed trousers, and his distinctive patent-leather shoes with spats. He also wore a few gleaming accessories[unicode 8212]an ornate signet ring on his little finger, a pair of sapphire cufflinks (a recent birthday present from myself), and a pocket-watch on a chain which was a family heirloom and very precious to him.[or]Poirot noticed me staring at him and stared back for a moment, looking bemused. I flustered and averted my gaze.[or]I kept my gaze carefully averted from Poirot for now, not wishing to embarrass myself further.[stopping]".




