The description of the p refrigerator is "Thanks to Poirot's extraordinary professional success, as well as my own respectable savings, we had been able to afford some of the most advanced devices of the time. The refrigerator was a marvel of technology and I already struggled to imagine life without it.[paragraph break]My friend's eating habits were still as queer as ever; for breakfast, alongside his drinking chocolate and the occasional French pastry, he typically had toast made from a square loaf of bread[unicode 8212]which he then cut into smaller, perfectly even squares[unicode 8212]and two eggs which must be of the exact same size. His grocer had taken to sorting out a special box of matched eggs, for which Poirot has been immensely grateful.".

