The description of the television is "An incredible device which the children had welcomed with no small amount of excitement. I myself had been very glad for the ability to watch the Wimbledon Championships the previous year despite having to stay home due to an ill-timed bout of fever. Recently there had been a film broadcast which featured renowned actress Mary Marvell[unicode 8212]a former client of Poirot whose case I had assisted with[unicode 8212]and I had revelled in the children's awe and wonder on learning of my past association with her. [paragraph break]Despite his stated disinterest in most of the current programming, Poirot sometimes found his way down to our flat to watch something with us. (Coincidentally, I am writing these words on the very day that our television service resumed, after a years-long wartime interruption.)[line break]".


