	increase the Browsing Count by 1;
	if the Browsing Count is at least 8:
		say "Tempting as it was to continue reading, I decided I should take a break and go about my business." instead;
	say "I perused the shelves and indiscriminately chose a story to read from.[paragraph break][italic type]";
	if the Browsing Count is 6:
		say "'No,' he said gently. 'I did not drink it. While my good friend Hastings was apostrophizing the night, I took the opportunity of pouring it, not down my throat, but into a little bottle. That little bottle will go to the analytical chemist. No'—as the doctor made a sudden movement—'as a sensible man, you will understand that violence will be of no avail. During Hastings[apostrophe] brief absence to fetch you, I have had time to put the bottle in safe keeping. Ah, quick, Hastings, hold him!'

I misunderstood Poirot's anxiety. Eager to save my friend, I flung myself in front of him. But the doctor's swift movement had another meaning. His hand went to his mouth, a smell of bitter almonds filled the air, and he swayed forward and fell.";
	if the Browsing Count is 5:
		say "Poirot and I flattened ourselves against the wall. I heard a man's breathing as he passed us. Then he flashed on his torch, and as he did so, Poirot hissed in my ear:

		'Allez.'

		We sprang together, Poirot with a quick movement enveloped the intruder's head with a light woollen scarf whilst I pinioned his arms. The whole affair was quick and noiseless. I twisted a dagger from his hand, and as Poirot brought down the scarf from his eyes, whilst keeping it wound tightly round his mouth, I jerked up my revolver where he could see it and understand that resistance was useless.";
	if the Browsing Count is 1:
		say "'What a number of bond robberies there have been lately!' I observed one morning, laying aside the newspaper. 'Poirot, let us forsake the science of detection, and take to crime instead!'

		'You are on the[unicode 8212]how do you say it?[unicode 8212]get-rich-quick tack, eh, mon ami?'

		'Well, look at this last coup, the million dollars[apostrophe] worth of Liberty Bonds which the London and Scottish Bank were sending to New York, and which disappeared in such a remarkable manner on board the Olympia.'

		'If it were not for the mal de mer, and the difficulty of practising the so excellent method of Laverguier for a longer time than the few hours of crossing the channel, I should delight to voyage myself on one of these big liners,' murmured Poirot dreamily.";
	if the Browsing Count is 2:
