Check taking the leash:
	if Bob is leashed:
		say "I was already holding [dynamic name of Bob]'s leash." instead;
	if Bob is excited:
		now Bob is leashed;
		now the player is holding the leash;
		say "I took the leash from [dynamic name of Bob] and clipped it onto his collar. He snorted excitedly and gave the leash a light tug, but upon being called to heel he sat at my feet obediently." instead;
	if Bob is satisfied:
		say "For the time being, I had no more use for the leash." instead.
	
Smiling is an action applying to nothing. Understand "smile" as smiling.
Carry out smiling:
	say "I was cheerful and felt a great smile on my face.".
	
Crying is an action applying to nothing. Understand "cry" and "sob" and "weep" and "frown" as crying.
Carry out crying:
	say "I felt I had done entirely too much of that already, and was looking ahead to happier days.".

Understand "Arthur", "Hastings" and "Arthur Hastings" as yourself.

Instead of examining yourself:
	if a mirror is visible:
		say "[if the player is wearing the necktie]Looking at myself in the mirror, I absentmindedly patted my hair and adjusted my tie.[else]Looking at myself in the mirror, I absentmindedly patted my hair and adjusted my collar.";
		now the necktie is crooked;
	otherwise:
		say "I looked down at myself and took a moment to straighten out my clothes.";
		now the necktie is crooked.
		



		
