Talking to is an action applying to one thing. Understand "TALK TO [something]", "talk [something]", "speak [something]", "speak to [something]", "chat [something]", "chat with [something]", "converse with [something]", "listen [something]", "greet [something]", "listen to [something]" and "T [something]" as talking to.

Report talking to:
	if the noun is not a person, say "I explained some theories aloud to [the noun], which of course stayed silent.".
	
Report talking to yourself:
	say "I mused aloud about various thoughts and theories.".
	
