The pullover is a backdrop. Understand "pullover", "sleeveless", "patterned", "sleeveless pullover", "pull-over", "pull", "pul", "jum", "jump", "sweater" and "jumper" as the pullover. The pullover is everywhere.
The description of the pullover is "A patterned red-and-beige pullover; an old favourite of mine, and very soft.".

The mackintosh is a backdrop. Understand "mackintosh", "coat", "mack" and "mac" as the mackintosh. The mackintosh is everywhere.
The umbrella is a backdrop. Understand "umb", "umbrella" and "brella" as the umbrella. The umbrella is everywhere.

The description of the mackintosh is "A coat I liked to keep in my flat for walks like these.".
The description of the umbrella is "A plain black umbrella; essential on days like to-day.".

Does the player mean doing something to the p stand: it is very likely.
Does the player mean doing something to the h stand: it is very likely.
Does the player mean doing something to the coffee maker: it is very likely.




